<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="89" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,222,248]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Discussion:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[396,494,223,249]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">holotype</typeStatus>
is a brachypterous female (
<figureCitation box="[813,953,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–38" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1057,1081]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,525,1034]" captionTargetId="figure-178@16.[164,1423,525,1034]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 35–38. Cryphocricos schubarti (35) holotype, dorsal and (36) allotype, ventral. Cryphocricos vianai holotype (37) dorsal and (38) ventral. Fig. 35 and C. vianai photos courtesy of H.D.D. Rodrigues." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693114/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Figs. 37–38</figureCitation>
). The junior synonym, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1951" box="[1221,1332,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montei">
<emphasis box="[1221,1332,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">C. montei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was described based on a single brachypterous male from Escaramuça, 
<collectingCountry box="[905,975,259,285]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Brasil</collectingCountry>
, which is located ca. 
<quantity box="[1230,1304,258,285]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" unit="km" value="50.0">50 km</quantity>
NNE from Ribeirão Preto in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[497,615,295,321]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1951" box="[629,861,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vianai">
<emphasis box="[629,861,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Cryphocricos vianai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found in lotic habitats in 
<collectingRegion box="[1276,1432,295,321]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,219,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="de Souza, M. A. A. &amp; de Melo, A. L. &amp; Vianna, G. J. C." box="[235,470,331,358]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="803 - 810" refId="ref12626" refString="de Souza, M. A. A., de Melo, A. L. &amp; Vianna, G. J. C. (2006) Heteroipteros aquaiticos oriundos do Municiipio de Mariana, MG. Neotropical Entomology, 35 (6), 803 - 810. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1519 - 566 X 2006000600013" type="journal article" year="2006">
de Souza 
<emphasis box="[346,403,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
), including only in the streams around the Serra da Canastra but not in the mountains, although it is known from some mountain streams in the Serra do Cipó (
<bibRefCitation author="Pelli, A. &amp; Nieser, N. &amp; de Melo, A. L." box="[951,1133,367,394]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="67 - 72" refId="ref13534" refString="Pelli, A., Nieser, N. &amp; de Melo, A. L. (2006) Nepomorpha and Gerromorpha (Insecta: Heteroptera) from the Serra da Canastra, southwestern Minas Gerais state, Brazil. Lundiana, 7 (1), 67 - 72." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pelli 
<emphasis box="[1010,1066,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was reported to occur in mountain streams with fair to strong current with a pebble or stone substrate (
<bibRefCitation author="de Melo, A. L. &amp; Nieser, N." box="[1153,1425,403,429]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="43 - 49" refId="ref12575" refString="de Melo, A. L. &amp; Nieser, N. (2004) Faunistical notes on aquatic Heteroptera of Minas Gerais (Brazil): an annotated list of Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha collected near Januaria, MG. Lundiana, 5 (1), 43 - 49." type="journal article" year="2004">de Melo &amp; Nieser 2004</bibRefCitation>
). In a study to determine the effect of physico-chemical variables on aquatic Heteropteran communities in streams in 
<collectingRegion box="[180,328,475,501]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[340,411,475,501]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1951" box="[422,688,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vianai">
<emphasis box="[422,574,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Cryphocricos</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[618,688,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">vianai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found only in a preserved stream and not in degraded streams (
<bibRefCitation author="Dias-Silva, K. &amp; Cabette, H. S. R. &amp; Juen, L. &amp; de Marco Jr, P." box="[159,413,511,537]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="918 - 930" refId="ref12692" refString="Dias-Silva, K., Cabette, H. S. R., Juen, L. &amp; de Marco Jr, P. (2010) The influence of habitat integrity and physical-chemical water variables on the structure of aquatic and semi-aquatic Heteroptera. Zoologia, 27 (6), 918 - 930. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1984 - 46702010000600013" type="journal article" year="2010">
Dias-Silva 
<emphasis box="[287,344,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The fifth instar was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopez Ruf, M. L." box="[812,1014,511,537]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="103 - 120" refId="ref13109" refString="Lopez Ruf, M. L. (1991) El genero Cryphocricos en la Argentina (Hemiptera-Limnocoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 49 (1 - 4), 103 - 120." type="journal article" year="1991">Lopez Ruf (1991)</bibRefCitation>
based on a single specimen from the type locality. The genital capsule was described in general for the genus and the flagellum of the aedeagus of a 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1951" box="[345,447,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vianai">
<emphasis box="[345,447,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">C. vianai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
measured 
<quantity box="[569,648,583,609]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[662,833,582,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="101 - 106" refId="ref12436" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1965). Segmentos genitales y contenido de la capsula genital en machos de especies de los generos Ambrysus, Pelocoris, Limnocoris, Heleocoris y Cryphocricos (Hemiptera - Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 27, 101 - 106. [1964]" type="journal article" year="1965">De Carlo 1965</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="89" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,618,644]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1940" box="[772,862,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis box="[772,862,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">C. rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dark-brown color, the conspicuous wrinkles on the mesosternum, and the lack of granulation (=tubercles) on the hemelytra and scutellum (
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[1204,1374,654,681]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref12376" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1951) I) Nueva agrupacion en subgeneros de las especies del genero Abedus Stal (Hemipt. Belostom.). II) Descripcion de dos especies nuevas del genero Cryphocricos (Hemipt. Naucor.). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 15, 69 - 76." type="journal article" year="1951">De Carlo 1951</bibRefCitation>
). In a treatment of species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[409,561,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[409,561,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Cryphocricos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known or thought to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[894,1008,691,717]" name="Argentina" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopez Ruf, M. L." box="[1018,1217,691,717]" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" pagination="103 - 120" refId="ref13109" refString="Lopez Ruf, M. L. (1991) El genero Cryphocricos en la Argentina (Hemiptera-Limnocoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 49 (1 - 4), 103 - 120." type="journal article" year="1991">Lopez Ruf (1991)</bibRefCitation>
provided a detailed diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1951" box="[304,406,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vianai">
<emphasis box="[304,406,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="89">C. vianai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although it was not comparative.
</paragraph>
